  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 .

oakcurric:unit-28
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Geometrical properties: similarity and Pythagoras' theorem"@en ;
  curric:slug "geometrical-properties-similarity-and-pythagoras-theorem" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores the concepts of congruence and similarity, and ways to prove or
  disprove similarity between shapes. We then explore further properties of triangles with
  Pythagoras' Theorem."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on knowledge developed in work on transformations, angles
  and properties of triangles. Pupils explored the effects of different transformations and
  whether the transformed shape was congruent or similar to the original shape. This knowledge
  is built upon and applied to new contexts as pupils formalise the criteria for determining
  congruence in triangles and study rotational symmetry. This unit also prepares pupils for
  learning about trigonometry to extend a right-angled triangle in the unit circle to any other
  right-angled triangle.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-28-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-28-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-28-3 ;
  curric:id "28"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.728412Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-24
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Numerical summaries of data"@en ;
  curric:slug "numerical-summaries-of-data" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils explore the concept of measures of central tendancy,
  developing understanding of different types of average and their relative benefits and
  drawbacks. We then investigate other summaries of data such as the range and data
  comparison techniques."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Building on work pupils have undertaken on averages in key stage 2, and
  linking to the previous unit where we summarised data graphically, pupils now explore
  representing data numerically. Pupils focus on the concept of measures of central tendency
  and range. We also begin to look at correlation as a relationship between data.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-24-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-24-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-24-3 ;
  curric:id "24"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.437283Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-statistics .

oakcurric:unit-26
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Geometrical properties: polygons"@en ;
  curric:slug "geometrical-properties-polygons" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will investigate internal and external angles of polygons and
  angles made with a transveral and parallel lines. Pupils will develop their ability to
  formally prove properties of polygons to generalise."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on knowledge developed investigating angles and continues
  work done in the previous unit investigating polygons. Here pupils will develop understanding
  of external and internal angles of polygons and traversals through parallel lines""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-26-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-26-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-26-3 ;
  curric:id "26"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.029694Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-17
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Transformations"@en ;
  curric:slug "transformations" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces pupils to shape tranformations: enlargements, rotations,
  reflections and translations both by hand and with technology."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit utilises prior knowledge with ratios and percentages, applying
  general multiplicative relationships to the transformation of shapes, whilst also drawing
  upon recently developed knowledge of the coordinate plane.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-17-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-17-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-17-3 ;
  curric:id "17"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.059222Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-29
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Probability: possible outcomes"@en ;
  curric:slug "probability-possible-outcomes" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces and explores the concept of liklihood as a relative measure,
  and demonstrates multiple ways to represent likelihood such as Venn diagrams, tree
  diagrams and two-way tables."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit is the first introduction to probability and likelihood. Pupils
  develop their understanding of how likely something is, looking at relative likelihoods and
  displaying outcomes but without formalising probability using measurable numerical values at
  this stage. Pupils explore different ways to display outcomes to gain a sense of what it
  means to say something is likely or unlikely in preparation for more calculative methods and
  theoretical probability in the next unit.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-29-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-29-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-29-3 ;
  curric:id "29"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.165818Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-probability .

oakcurric:unit-34
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Standard form"@en ;
  curric:slug "standard-form" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils learn to recognise, interpret and write in standard form.
  Pupils then extend this knowledge so that they can order numbers written in standard form."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds from arithmetic procedures with integers and decimals. In
  the prior unit, pupils learnt how to factorise multiples of 10 in order to simplify
  calculations. This understanding is further developed in this unit as values are converted to
  meet the conditions for standard form.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-34-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-34-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-34-3 ;
  curric:id "34"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.303629Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number .

oakcurric:unit-30
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Probability: theoretical probabilities"@en ;
  curric:slug "probability-theoretical-probabilities" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit we build upon the concept of likelihood to work more mathematically
  with more measurable probability using fraction and decimal representations to both
  interpret and calculate. We revisit and develop ways to represent and compare
  probabilities."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Further to developing the basic ideas and foundations of probability, we
  move towards more abstract measures of likelihood using calculations to assign numerical
  values to probability. We then revisit the visual models of probability established in the
  previous unit through the lens of representing and utilising theoretical probability.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-30-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-30-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-30-3 ;
  curric:id "30"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.320431Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-probability .

oakcurric:unit-25
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Perimeter, area and volume"@en ;
  curric:slug "perimeter-area-and-volume" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils extend their knowledge of shapes by exploring the properties
  of circles and composite shapes before developing understanding of 3-D shapes including
  surface area and volume."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit is an extension of the perimeter and area unit in year 7 (which
  focused on polygons), and extends this knowledge to focus on circles and circle based
  composite shapes then extending to look at the concept of prisms and volume.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-25-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-25-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-25-3 ;
  curric:id "25"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.348052Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure ,
    oakcurric:thread-number .

