oakcurric:unit-19
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Sequences"@en ;
  curric:slug "sequences" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit we develop knowledge of sequences to be able to identify, determine,
  and continue arithmetic sequences. We finish the unit by looking at how sequences may be
  reprsented graphically."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit pupils are developing their knowledge of plotting coordinates
  by exploring the idea that a set of points can satisfy a mathematical relationship. This unit
  sets the foundation for working with graphical representations of linear equations.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-19-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-19-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-19-3 ;
  curric:id "19"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.374224Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-21
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Solving linear equations"@en ;
  curric:slug "solving-linear-equations" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will learn how to find a value that satisfies a linear
  relationship when one value is known both with a single step operation, and multiple step
  operations. A variety of cases are explored including using brackets and rearranging."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Further to graphing linear sequences in the previous unit, pupils now
  learn to connect understanding with solving linear equations after demonstrating how for each
  point on a linear graph there is a unique solution to the equation of the line.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-21-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-21-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-21-3 ;
  curric:id "21"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.376680Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-33
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Trigonometry"@en ;
  curric:slug "trigonometry" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils learn how to recognise the relationship between the unit
  circle and the trigonometric ratios of sine, cosine and tangent. Pupils then apply this
  knowledge to solve trigonometric problems."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils have recently learned about geometrical properties of similarity
  and the Pythagorean Theorem. This knowledge is further developed to build on their
  understanding of congruence and similarity with right-angled triangles. In this unit,
  similarity is used to extend a right-angled triangle in the unit circle to any other
  right-angled triangle.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-33-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-33-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-33-3 ;
  curric:id "33"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.378855Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure ,
    oakcurric:thread-ratio-and-proportion .

oakcurric:unit-14
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Comparing and ordering fractions and decimals (positive and negative)"@en ;
  curric:slug "comparing-and-ordering-fractions-and-decimals-positive-and-negative" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit develops understanding and manipulation of fractions, including
  conversion between fractions to terminating and recurring decimals. Pupils then learn
  strategies to order fractions of increasing complexity."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds upon work done in the 'arithmetic procedures with
  integers and decimals' unit, supporting further development of fluency in working with
  decimals as well as fractions.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-14-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-14-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-14-3 ;
  curric:id "14"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.411970Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number .

oakcurric:unit-13
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Perimeter and area"@en ;
  curric:slug "perimeter-and-area" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils investigate how to calculate the area and perimeter of
  rectilinear shapes, and composite shapes using rectangles and triangles. They will also
  derive simple area formulae."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit requires some confidence in the use of formulae and simple
  algebra, hence it has been positioned after pupils have done some work on algebraic
  manipulation and number operations. This unit also prepares pupils for further work on
  geometry later in the year.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-13-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-13-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-13-3 ;
  curric:id "13"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.414200Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-8
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Properties of number: factors, multiples, squares and cubes"@en ;
  curric:slug "properties-of-number-factors-multiples-squares-and-cubes" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils develop their understanding of factors and multiples, then
  extend this knowledge to learn general divisibility tests for integers and develop
  strategies to determine the highest common factor and lowest common multiple of two or
  more integers."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit continues to develop proficiency in handling and recognising
  different types of numbers, as well as understanding their mathematical structure in order to
  be more efficient and fluent with mathematical operations in the following unit.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-8-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-8-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-8-3 ;
  curric:id "8"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.428094Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number .

oakcurric:unit-11
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Expressions and equations"@en ;
  curric:slug "expressions-and-equations" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn about generalisation and formal algebraic manipulation
  techniques such as substitution, collecting like terms and factorising."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit is a natural extension of the number work in the previous units.
  We are now seeking to generalise patterns and behaviours that were first seen in the number
  units taught before, and pulling in key skills such as factorisation and multiplication of
  brackets as part of algebraic manipulation.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-11-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-11-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-11-3 ;
  curric:id "11"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.430690Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-35
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Graphical representations"@en ;
  curric:slug "graphical-representations" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils draw, interpret and utilise linear graphs to solve problems.
  This knowledge is further extended to look at intersecting graphs."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds knowledge from previous work on non-linear relationships.
  In that unit, pupils considered geometric sequences and how they might be represented
  graphically. In this unit, pupils study the graphical representation to link features of the
  graph to its equation.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-35-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-35-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-35-3 ;
  curric:id "35"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.475531Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-12
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Plotting coordinates"@en ;
  curric:slug "plotting-coordinates" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils revisit and further develop their understanding of the
  coordinate plane, and learn how to plot non-integer coordinates. Pupils then plot from an
  equation both by hand and by using technology."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Continuing from their recent work using algebra, this unit introduces
  plotting from algebraic equations and developing generalisations from a set of coordinate
  pairs.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-12-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-12-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-12-3 ;
  curric:id "12"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.513258Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-2584
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Thinking critically with maths"@en ;
  curric:slug "thinking-critically-with-maths" ;
  rdfs:comment "[TO BE ADDED]"@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow "[TO BE ADDED]" ;
