oakcurric:unit-20
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Graphical representations of linear equations"@en ;
  curric:slug "graphical-representations-of-linear-equations" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unti we develop understanding of linear relationships and explore the key
  features of a linear equation such as the gradient, intercept and determining an equation
  from coordinate pairs."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit we continue to build on knowledge developed in the previous
  work on sequences and build confidence in how a linear sequence produces a linear
  relationship. We represent that graphically along with development of understanding of the
  equation of a line, positive, negative relationships and the idea that a linear sequence can
  produce an infinite set of points.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-20-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-20-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-20-3 ;
  curric:id "20"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.541575Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-31
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Non-linear relationships"@en ;
  curric:slug "non-linear-relationships" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit we explore geometric and special number sequences like the Fibonacci
  sequence. We develop strategies to recognise types of sequence and continue them."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds from the sequences unit in Year 8. We develop
  understanding of sequences further to look at geometric and other non-linear sequences and
  how they appear graphically.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-31-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-31-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-31-3 ;
  curric:id "31"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.555467Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-27
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Constructions"@en ;
  curric:slug "constructions" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit we develop skills in using a pair of compasses and ruler to construct
  various accurate shapes and angles including triangles, rhombi, perpendicular lines and
  angle bisectors."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """After studying polygons and circles in depth in previous units, this year
  culminates in learning to mathematically construct these shapes using knowledge of the
  properties of triangles, quadrilaterals and circles in order to draw them accurately.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-27-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-27-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-27-3 ;
  curric:id "27"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.590013Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-22
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Understanding multiplicative relationships: percentages and proportionality"@en ;
  curric:slug "understanding-multiplicative-relationships-percentages-and-proportionality" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils explore multiplicative relationships with percentages, direct
  and inverse proportion."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils build upon key stage 2 work with finding percentages of amounts,
  then extending their knowledge to percentage change, connecting to previous learning around
  decimals and fractions. Pupils then explore a more general exploration of multiplicative
  relationships.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-22-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-22-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-22-3 ;
  curric:id "22"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.592415Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-ratio-and-proportion ,
    oakcurric:thread-number .

oakcurric:unit-3777
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Calculator functionality"@en ;
  curric:slug "calculator-functionality" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit teaches how to use scientific calculators and expores their
  functionality"""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """It is important to dedicate some time to understanding the functionality
  of modern scientific calculators so that they can be used appropriately.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3777-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3777-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3777-3 ;
  curric:id "3777"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.634970Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 .

oakcurric:unit-32
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Expressions and formulae"@en ;
  curric:slug "expressions-and-formulae" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit develops pupil understanding of formulae and how to rearrange them.
  Pupils will learn how to recognise and manipulate binomials and learn to recognise the
  difference of two squares."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on solving linear equations from year 7 where pupils
  learnt to rearrange aan equation to find a specific value that satisfied the equation. In
  expressions and formulae, pupils use their understanding of rearrangement to change the
  subject of a formula. Pupils are then introduced binomial equations in preparation for
  trigonometry.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-32-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-32-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-32-3 ;
  curric:id "32"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.640768Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

