  (e.g. distance when walking or flying)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.638477Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-283-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A bar model can be used to find the original amount after a percentage decrease."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.638481Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-283-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A double number line can be used to find the original amount after a percentage
  decrease."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.638486Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-283-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A ratio table can be used to find the original amount after a percentage
  decrease."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.638490Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-283-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In all of these representations a single multiplier can be used to find the original
  amount after a percentage decrease."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.638494Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

